{
  "stem": "232.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were waiting for a smuggler.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I forgot to mention-- and it was a few years back, 1933.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was eight years old.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My grandparents, my mother's father and mother, lived in Berlin, too.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were very religious, I mean, observant and religious.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When he goes to the temple, you're not allowed to carry anything.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I was the, the grandchild, the oldest grandchild, the boy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So he took me to the synagogue to carry his tallit, you know, the shawl, the prayer shawl.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we came from the-- this was a Friday night-- we came from the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And while we were walking, it was-- it was dark.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The street was not very, very-- there was not very many people on it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But from far, we saw two SS men on each side of the sidewalk walking, with the black boots, with the black uniforms, and the swastika on the-- with the whole uniform, two on each side of the sidewalk.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my grandfather, when he saw this, he took me on his hand.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he walked down from the sidewalk in the street, not to bother them so they can pass.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At this moment, both-- from both sides, the four guys approached, came to my grandfather, and pulled out the night sticks and started beating him up.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was severely beaten.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I started screaming and crying until some neighbors came out and called the number.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then he was taken to the hospital.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So this was one episode I want to mention.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was in 1933.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] [DRINKS] To continue, on our trip to-- our trip-- our [LAUGHS] exodus from Germany to Belgium, we walked, like I said, the whole night.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
